# (Create this in Unity and track it in Git)

MyUnityGame/
├── Assets/
│   ├── Art/
│   ├── Audio/
│   ├── Prefabs/
│   ├── Scenes/
│   ├── Scripts/
│   └── UI/
├── ProjectSettings/
├── Packages/
└── .gitignore

---

# How to Collaborate (Simplified)

1. One person creates the repo and pushes the full Unity project (minus ignored files).
2. Others clone the repo.
3. Both of yall use Unity Hub to open the project.
4. When you make changes:
   - `git pull` to get your friend's work
   - Make your edits
   - `git add .`, `git commit -m "what you changed"`, then `git push`
5. Never edit the same scene at the same time. Use prefabs or split the level into multiple scenes.

# You're ready to cook.
